&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term - 6 months from start of contract &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to contribute to the delivery of a first class learning and educational experience, within a dynamic education team? The Clinical Education department are looking for an enthusiastic Registered Nurse or Allied Health Professional who has substantial experience at Band 5 or above.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within our department as a Clinical Educator; you will have previous experience of delivering excellent patient care and have a passion for education. You will have demonstrable evidence of having delivered or taken part in teaching within a variety of contexts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within Clinical Skills, Resuscitation and Simulation you will support the Clinical Leads in the design and delivery of educational programmes, ensuring patient safety is at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent communication skills, work well within a small team and have a passion to continually improve practice through education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
